metadata.name: Cymru #73
metadata.description:

Use number keys to render at different sizes.

metadata.name: The Great Annihilator #87
metadata.description:
One day you wake up,
All words are meaningless
And you can feel the light inside your mouth
Where everything were assembled and annihilated
Swallow the air, swallow all particle
A taste of burnt metal and ethyl
One thousand years of living souls
And you, are no more



=========

Controls:

[1] Set resolution to 716 x 1024px (default)

[2] Set resolution to 1433 x 2048px

[3] Set resolution to 2688 x 3840px

* The presets above are suitable for screen viewing up to 4k screen resolution. To set a custom resolution for printing and other purpose, add &res=[desired resolution] at the end of the URL. It will set the height of the image, and the width will be calculated automatically at 0.7 ratio. For example to get a resolution of 4911 x 7016px (about the size of A2 paper), add &res=7016 as URL parameter.

[c] Capture a screenshot at rendered resolution


Notes:

* This project use shaders that relies on GPU. Hi-res output may slow down your device. Since it also utilize GPU instance for thumbnail rendering, expect longer time for every iterations to be signed by fx(hash).

* If 'glitching' occurs or the composition behaves differently at different resolution, just refresh the page to reset it.

Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment

XALTED 2023

metadata.name: Smooth Steps #74
metadata.description:
Mostly dark. 

Custom software (color, silent) Variable dimensions, horizontal or vertical HTML, JavaScript, WebGL

Keys

i : Toggle info
1-4 : Display density (select 1 if slow)
q : Toggle quality
f : Full-screen

Some settings can be adjusted through the URL query string: more info in the HTML source.

metadata.name: Unlocked #4
metadata.description:
The 'unlocked' collection is inspired by the unlock patterns available on many smartphones. Even if this functionality is disappearing in favor of biometric identification, I loved it and wanted to create something around it.

Two grid sizes are available: 4x4 and 5x5. The number of lines is also generated by the hash and varies between 8 and 15.

metadata.name: Angular Waves #31
metadata.description:
Changes in viewing angle can reveal or postpone story information, introduce a specific location or mood, or create visual variety.
In fact, every angle of view alters the mood, rhythm, and even the fictional events in the space.
With changes in the viewing angle, the image's emotional and visual characteristics change, and with those changes, the implicit meaning of the work changes as well.
Viewing angles are affected by the visual experiences of everyday life, which contribute to their semantic load.
In the same way, what a person learns from his surroundings is stored in his mind and used to understand and interpret an image.
Made by p5.js
